data.text: @Mau_Keta All goods! I just learnt myself today that it was important to report back negative results.

@Mau_Keta Yup. I’m that c*** 😂🤦🏽‍♂️

The worlds clearly a better place for the negatives over the years.
@raaniera Haha I’ve done similar tests to this 👀😂 but tbh more anxious about those than this 😅
@Mau_Keta 😂😂😂 its the red, for sure. Other tests 👀⚫️🔵 have never caused such anxiety 😅
@raaniera True. Defs can understand how the nerves set in seeing that red in the initial stages 😬🚨

@Mau_Keta So far I’ve returned two negative RAT’s 😷

The initial WTF when the red is running is next level hopohopo/dread 😳😵‍💫
@takaramaina Maitaki rahi e hoa. I just did it now
@Mau_Keta Don't forget to report on My Covid your test result is negative e hoa

@NickManarangi Control and test. 

Control refers to the actual test being successful or not. And the T refers to whether covid was detected in the sample. 

So C ONLY = negative covid result 
C + T = positive.
@Dawmaiden @Mau_Keta I would assume ‘Control’ and ‘Test’. If the C doesn’t show a line then it hasn’t worked properly and you should repeat, if the T shows a line you are positive
